UX goals for QA engineers (layout/content priorities)

Apply across shell + high-traffic routes (projects, requirements, test-cases, runs, reporting):





Information density with scanability: stable column sets, zebra/hover row states, sticky header row for long tables, compact vs comfortable density toggle (implemented with Tamagui Stack/XStack/YStack + themed row components).



Traceability-first navigation: persistent project context (existing [ProjectPicker](apps/web/src/components/ProjectPicker)); add breadcrumbs and “back to list” patterns on detail pages.



Run workflow clarity: status chips, filters (release/sprint/environment), bulk actions where the API allows; reserve primary actions for “create run”, “add result”, “open traceability”.



Low-friction keyboard/mouse: focus rings, skip link (already in shell), sensible tab order in forms and tables.



Testing contract: keep and extend data-testid on interactive and assertable regions (Playwright-first); avoid coupling tests to generated class names; prefer roles where stable.

Implementation approach (web)





Dependencies & setup: Add tamagui, @tamagui/vite-plugin (or the current recommended Vite integration from Tamagui docs), and any starter packages the docs prescribe for React 19. Wire TamaguiProvider in [apps/web/src/main.tsx](apps/web/src/main.tsx) alongside BrowserRouter and urql Provider. Configure Vite in [apps/web/vite.config.ts](apps/web/vite.config.ts) for the compiler plugin and any optimizeDeps exclusions Tamagui requires.



tamagui.config.ts: Define tokens (space, radius, color palettes) and themes including semantic run colors (pass/fail/skip/blocked) and neutral surfaces; this file becomes the contract for a future Expo app.



Shell first: Rebuild [AppShell](apps/web/src/layout/AppShell.tsx) with Tamagui layout + Text/Button/Anchor (or Link from react-router wrapped in styled Tamagui); map banners into themed Card/SizableText/Paragraph while preserving existing data-testids so current E2E keeps working.



Page rollout (incremental): List pages first (projects, requirements, test cases, runs), then detail pages. Build list/table UIs as composable rows (virtualization optional later if lists grow). Replace global CSS incrementally; delete or narrow App.css / AppShell.css only as each region migrates.



Forms & dialogs: Use Tamagui form primitives + sheets/dialogs per docs; keep validation UX consistent with API fixHint patterns already shown in the shell.

Sample project with multiple requirements and tests

Goal: One command produces a rich demo dataset for demos and manual QA without clicking through the UI.





Preferred: Add a root-level script (e.g. scripts/seed-demo-qa-project.ts) run with tsx, using the same domain/service layer the GraphQL resolvers use ([TcmsService](src/domain/service.ts) / [createDb](src/db/client.ts)) against a chosen DB_PATH (default dev DB or an explicit path). The script should:





createProject with a fixed key like DEMO-QA



Create N requirements with varied status/priority/tags



Create manual and automated test cases with steps



Create requirement↔test links and optional automated↔manual links



Optionally create a test run with mixed results for reporting screens



Expose: npm run seed:demo in root [package.json](package.json) (document in [docs/LOCAL_MANUAL_TESTING.md](docs/LOCAL_MANUAL_TESTING.md)).



Optional dev-only UI: A “Load sample data” button on home/dev settings is nice-to-have but increases scope; the script keeps MVP boundaries clear.

Testing suite for UI

Primary (extend what you have): Playwright remains the contract for “real UI + real API + SQLite”:





Add/extend specs after layout migration to assert navigation, filters, and critical empty/error states still work; keep @smoke tags coherent with [apps/web/package.json](apps/web/package.json) scripts.



Consider a second Playwright project for mobile viewport (e.g. devices['Pixel 5']) targeting shell + one list + one detail flow—aligns with Tamagui’s responsive goals before Expo exists.

Secondary (optional): Vitest + React Testing Library in apps/web for isolated components (e.g. ProjectPicker, filter bars) with urql mocking—matches [.notes/FE_MVP_SPEC.md](.notes/FE_MVP_SPEC.md) and complements Playwright.

Not required initially: Visual snapshot testing—only add if flaky-rate stays acceptable.

Documentation in .wiki (after implementation approval)

Per git-wiki skill, add concise pages with YAML frontmatter and link from [.wiki/index.md](.wiki/index.md):





.wiki/concepts/ui-qa-layout-tamagui-and-mobile.md — UX principles, Tamagui choice, Expo/RN path (shared config + operations), table strategy tradeoffs.



.wiki/flows/seed-demo-qa-project.md — how to run seed:demo, what entities it creates, safety notes (DB_PATH).



.wiki/features/apps-web-ui-testing.md — Playwright layout, smoke tags, optional Vitest/RTL scope.

Note: Full wiki ingest is git-HEAD-driven; these pages are manual architecture notes unless you later run an ingest pass to fold changed source files into feature pages.

Risks / mitigations





Compiler / Vite friction: Follow Tamagui’s current Vite guide; pin versions; add a minimal “tamagui smoke” page in dev if needed to validate the pipeline before wide migration.



Dense tables: Accept composed table layout first; add virtualization only if profiling shows need.



A11y: Tamagui exposes props for many primitives—explicitly set accessibilityRole / labels on native-bound components even on web where habits differ; keep skip link and landmark structure from the current shell.



Test stability: Prefer data-testid and role-based selectors; debounce or waitFor where animations affect visibility.

